{"word":"φρουρέω","slug":"φρουρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>φρουρέω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πρό\">πρό</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὁράω\">ὁράω</a></el> via <el>οὐρέω</el> ‘watch, guard’]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘maintain official watch’, <b>guard,</b> against an escape <b><a href='B:540 11:32'>2 Cor 11:32</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘provide security for’, <b>protect</b> against harm, in imagery <b><a href='B:570 4:7'>Phil 4:7</a>; <a href='B:670 1:5'>1 Pt 1:5</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>3.</pp></b> ‘hold in custody’, <b>detain, confine,</b> in imagery <b><a href='B:550 3:23'>Gal 3:23</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:φροντίζω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:φρυάσσω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}